Paige Jones is a professional rodeo contestant from Wayne, Oklahoma, specializing in barrel racing. She has been a member of the Women’s Professional Rodeo Association (WPRA) since 2020.

Jones has had a successful career in rodeo, with her career earnings through the 2023 regular season totaling $102,968.

Here you can follow Paige Jones’ net worth, career earnings, career highlights, horses, personal details, relationship status, and more.

About Paige Jones

Paige Jones was born on December 21, 2001, in Wayne, Oklahoma. She comes from a family with a passion for rodeo, with her sister Ceri also being a successful rodeo competitor.

Paige’s love for rodeo began at a young age, and she has been competing in various events, including barrel racing, pole bending, goat tying, and breakaway roping.

Early Career

Paige started her rodeo journey by participating in junior high and high school rodeos. She won multiple state titles and qualified for the National High School Rodeo Association (NHSRA) Finals multiple times.

Professional Career

Paige Jones has been a member of the Women’s Professional Rodeo Association (WPRA) since 2020.

She specializes in barrel racing and has had a successful career, with her career earnings through the 2023 regular season totaling $102,968.

Jones made her professional debut in 2020 during the height of the COVID-19 outbreak, which presented unique challenges for a rookie competitor. Despite these challenges, she finished the season as the Resistol Rookie of the Year and was 32nd in the world standings.

In 2021, she had a solid start to the season but pulled out early when one of her horses, High Cotton Lane, stopped performing as well as Jones knew he should.

In 2022, Jones had a promising season, winning several rodeos including the Tri-State Rodeo in Amarillo, Texas, and the Farm City Pro Rodeo in Hermiston, Oregon. She finished the year ranked 17th.

In 2023, she had major wins at Rodeo Houston, Wainwright Stampede in Alberta, Canada, Ponoka Stampede in Alberta, Canada, Cody Stampede in Wyoming, and Central Wyoming Fair & Rodeo in Casper. She qualified for the Wrangler National Finals Rodeo in 2023, starting in 15th place.

Her biggest rodeo win to date was at Cody, Wyoming, and her most memorable rodeo experience was winning Rookie of the Year.

Horses

Jones rides two horses in her competitions: Famous Hayday “Bazinga,” an 11-year-old gelding, and High Cotton Lane “Cotton,” a 9-year-old chestnut gelding.

Paige Jones’s Net Worth in 2023

As of 2023, Paige Jones’ net worth is estimated to be $1 million.

Her career earnings through the 2023 regular season amount to $242,390. This figure includes her winnings from various rodeo events and competitions.

Career Earnings

As a member of the Women’s Professional Rodeo Association (WPRA) since 2020, Paige’s career earnings through the 2023 regular season total $102,968.

Personal Details

Boyfriend

Paige is in a relationship. Her boyfriend is Less Lockwood. The couple shares beautiful pictures on Instagram.

How Old is Paige Jones?

She is 21 years old as of November 2023.

What is her nationality?

She is an American.
